<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: OCEANSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Oceanside man was in fair condition Monday after he was shot once in the 
chest by an unknown assailant, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Jason Eimers, 19, was shot about 6:30 p.m. Sunday after he answered a knock at 
his door in the 700 block of Flora Drive, Officer Chip Morin said. Eimers was 
taken to Scripps Memorial Hospital-La Jolla. The bullet was not removed and is 
lodged near his spine, Morin said. 
</P>
<P>
Although police said they have determined that the shooting was not 
gang-related, they do not have a motive or any suspects, Morin said. 
