<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: LAKESIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The president of the San Diego chapter of Hells Angels was sentenced Monday to 
five years in federal prison for possession of drugs. 
</P>
<P>
Guy Russell Castiglione, 40, of Lakeside, was also ordered to pay a $100,000 
fine. 
</P>
<P>
Castiglione pleaded guilty in December to possession of methamphetamine with 
intent to distribute. About two pounds of the drug were found in his 
girlfriend's purse on May 13. 
</P>
<P>
Sentencing for the girlfriend, Kathleen Pirelli, 21, also of Lakeside, was 
delayed until Thursday. She pleaded guilty to using a phone during a drug 
transaction. Her attorney said he would call Castiglione as a witness at her 
sentencing. 
</P>
<P>
Before imposing the sentence, U.S. District Judge John Rhoades said to 
Castiglione, "What do you have to say about mending your ways? You have a 
terrible record." 
</P>
<P>
"I don't have anything to say," Castiglione replied. 
</P>
<P>
Castiglione was convicted of racketeering in connection with the 1977 shooting 
deaths of three members of the rival Mongols motorcycle gang. He also has a 
previous drug conviction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
