<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAPID INCREASE IN POPULATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As per news item of Feb. 22, an increase of 250,000 people per day is 
frightening and mind-boggling. 
</P>
<P>
Poverty breeds uncontrollable population increase and unchecked population 
explosion perpetuates poverty. 
</P>
<P>
It is a vicious cycle. 
</P>
<P>
Britain, France, Spain, Belgium and Portugal are some of the old colonial 
powers who ruthlessly exploited their colonies and have done irreparable damage 
to their economies. Shouldn't this past colonial powers bear some 
responsibility for the mess they have left behind in their past colonies and 
help these poor nations in their struggle against population increase and 
poverty? 
</P>
<P>
It is in the interest of the whole world that all rich nations join the poor 
nations in their fight against this population menace. 
</P>
<P>
CHAITANYA DAVE 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Palos Verdes 
</P>
</TEXT>
