<HEADLINE>
<P>
NBA ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
OLAJUWON TOO MUCH FOR SPURS, ROBINSON IN ROCKET WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a match of the two best centers in the Western Conference, Akeem Olajuwon 
outperformed David Robinson and led the Houston Rockets to a 109-105 victory 
over the San Antonio Spurs Monday night at San Antonio. 
</P>
<P>
Olajuwon scored 14 of his 37 points in the fourth quarter, including a 15-foot 
jump shot with 39 seconds left that broke a 105-105 tie. 
</P>
<P>
He also had 14 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Mitchell Wiggins added two free throws with 11 seconds left to give the Rockets 
their sixth victory in 30 road games. 
</P>
<P>
Robinson scored 29 points for the Spurs, who had won four of their last six 
games. 
</P>
<P>
Miami 105, Utah 104 -- Glen Rice scored from the top of the key at the buzzer 
at Miami as the Heat ended the Jazz's seven-game winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
Rice's shot came on a pass from Sherman Douglas, who rebounded a missed shot by 
teammate Scott Haffner. 
</P>
<P>
The victory was the Heat's third in six games after winning just three of its 
previous 30. 
</P>
<P>
Rony Seikaly scored 25 points for the Heat and Douglas added 22 points and 14 
assists. 
</P>
<P>
Karl Malone scored 32 points for the Jazz and John Stockton added 21 points and 
14 assists. 
</P>
<P>
New Jersey 128, Sacramento 111 -- Chris Morris scored 22 points at East 
Rutherford, N.J., to lead the Nets, who had their best offensive performance of 
the season and won for only the third time in 21 games. 
</P>
<P>
Seven players scored in double figures for the Nets, whose previous high was 
117 points. Sam Bowie and Purvis Short each scored 20 points. 
</P>
<P>
Golden State 138, Charlotte 117 -- Mitch Richmond scored 30 points at Oakland 
as the Warriors handed the Hornets their 25th loss in 26 road games. 
</P>
<P>
Richmond scored 21 points in the third quarter. 
</P>
