<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
HOME RUNS LIFT ST. FRANCIS TO WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Home runs by Albert Ojeda and Matt Jones powered St. Francis High to a 7-3 
nonleague baseball win at South Pasadena on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
St. Francis (2-0) took the lead for good on Ojeda's two-run shot in the fourth 
inning that gave the Knights a 3-1 lead. Jones' solo shot in the seventh 
provided an insurance run. 
</P>
<P>
Starter Mitch Bowen (1-0), who struck out 11 and walked two in going the 
distance, joined the hit parade with three hits and a run batted in. 
</P>
<P>
In other baseball games: 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley 2, Crescenta Valley 1 -- Jack Cox hit a solo home run in the 
second and Kevin Branch pitched five scoreless innings as the Antelopes (1-1) 
posted a consolation-round victory in the Glendora tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Newbury Park 6, El Toro 3 -- Newbury Park scored six times with two out in the 
sixth to erase a 3-0 deficit in a consolation-round game of the Loara 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The Panthers (2-1-1) parlayed three consecutive El Toro errors and five hits 
into their biggest inning of the season. 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Poly 14, Eagle Rock 2 -- Catcher Kristie Faehnle hit her second home run of the 
season in a nonleague game at Poly. 
</P>
<P>
Faehnle's two-run shot in the third highlighted a four-run rally and gave the 
Parrots an 8-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Chaminade 11, Kennedy 0 -- Chaminade scored five runs in the third inning of a 
game at Granada Hills Recreation Center. 
</P>
<P>
Flintridge Sacred Heart 2, Village Christian 1 -- Flintridge Sacred Heart 
scored the winning run in the sixth inning on a sacrifice fly. 
</P>
<P>
Monroe 6, Taft 4 -- Losing pitcher Julie Kawamoto surrendered four walks and 
five runs in the first inning to visiting Monroe but allowed only one run in 
the next five innings. 
</P>
<P>
St. Bonaventure 3, Louisville 0 -- St. Bonaventure held the Royals to three 
hits in the nonleague game at home. 
</P>
<P>
Calabasas 14, St. Genevieve 1 -- Calabasas drew 14 walks and had 11 hits in the 
nonleague game at home. Kristi Thomsen was two for three with a double and 
triple. 
</P>
<P>
TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth 7, Bell 0 -- Chatsworth ran its record to 2-0 and did not allow 
visiting Bell to win a set in the nonleague match. 
</P>
<P>
VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Campbell Hall d. Montclair Prep, 15-2, 15-5, 13-15, 15-6 -- Will Fruehling had 
14 kills and three jump-serve aces for Campbell Hall (2-0) in a nonleague match 
against visiting Montclair Prep. Phil Bruno led Campbell Hall with eight solo 
blocks. 
</P>
