<HEADLINE>
<P>
JONES LEADS N. HOLLYWOOD AGAINST MATER DEI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
North Hollywood High, the newly crowned City Section 3-A Division basketball 
champion, plays tonight in the first round of the state Southern California 
Regionals against Mater Dei of Santa Ana, the Southern Section 5-AA champion. 
Tip-off is 7:30 at Ocean View High in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood (24-3) stunned favored Fremont in the City 3-A final Friday, 
76-71, behind senior center Dana Jones' 29 points, 29 rebounds and seven 
blocked shots. 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei (30-1), ranked No. 2 in the state by Cal-Hi Sports, defeated Loyola 
in the Southern Section 5-AA final Saturday at the Sports Arena, 83-57. The 
Monarchs, who have won Southern Section championships in six of the past eight 
seasons, are paced by Andy Karich, a 6-foot-6 off-guard who is averaging a 
team-high 15 points a game. 
</P>
<P>
The Monarchs' front line consists of 6-8 center Derek Stone, 6-7 forward 
Charlie Andres (15 points, 14 rebounds vs. Loyola) and 6-5 forward David Boyle 
(32 points, seven rebounds vs. Loyola). 
</P>
<P>
In a Division V game, Faith Baptist will play host to Calipatria of the San 
Diego Section at 7:30 p.m. Faith Baptist (19-10) defeated Brethren, 65-59, in 
overtime in the Southern Section 1-A Division championship game last Friday, 
winning the first basketball championship in school history. 
</P>
<P>
Calipatria, located near Brawley, lost to Christian of El Cajon, 65-48, in the 
San Diego Section Division V championship game Saturday. Calipatria was the 
top-seeded team in the division. 
</P>
<P>
Calipatria (21-4) is led by point guard Bernie Sotelo, a 5-10 senior who 
averages 12 points a game. Cesar Romero, a 6-foot senior forward, averages 10. 
It is not a big team -- the tallest starter is 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
In a Division I girls' game, Hart, the two-time defending Southern Section 5-A 
Division champion, plays host to San Diego Mt. Carmel, the San Diego Section 
Division I champion. 
</P>
<P>
Hart (25-4) came from behind to upset top-seeded Buena last Friday, 49-45. 
Sophomore guard Anjanette Dionne is averaging 23 points a game and 6-3 senior 
center Sara Wilson is averaging 19. 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel (22-5) defeated Santana, 56-55, last Friday. Forward Vicki de Jesus 
averages a team-high 17.5 points and 11 rebounds. Center Kris Grazzini (10.5 
points, 10 rebounds) will match up with Wilson. 
</P>
</TEXT>
