<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: MATTHEWS STUDIO BUYS TV EQUIPMENT COMPANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Matthews Studio Equipment Group, a Burbank company that makes and rents film 
production gear, said it has completed the acquisition of Innovative Television 
Equipment of Canoga Park for about $1.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
Innovative designs and manufactures equipment for television production and has 
annual sales of about $4 million, according to Matthews co-chairman Carlos De 
Mattos. 
</P>
<P>
Separately, Matthews said, its subsidiary, Hollywood Rental Co., agreed to 
acquire substantially all of the assets at the Burbank facility of Lee America 
West, a film production equipment company. Terms were not disclosed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
