<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUOTABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"I believe in decentralized theater. I believe there is no reason why any good 
theater should be bottle-necked in New York and Hollywood. I believe in a 
dramatic map for America that will include great native playhouses in every 
town large enough to want one." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Margo Jones, 1944, quoted in Helen Sheehy's "Margo: The Life and Theatre of 
Margo Jones" 
</P>
</TEXT>
