<P>
What Ortega Speech?: Technical problems were cited Monday as the reason that 
many Los Angeles viewers were not able to see a speech by Nicaraguan President 
Daniel Ortega that was supposed to be broadcast Saturday on the community 
access channels of local cable systems. According to Bill Rosendahl, vice 
president of Century Cable in Santa Monica, there were problems in pulling the 
signal down from the satellite. The speech did air in most places as planned, 
however. BETH KLEID 
