<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'Miss Saigon' Tops Olivier Nominations: "Miss Saigon" led the nominations for 
Britain's Laurence Olivier awards, England's equivalent of the Tony Awards. 
</P>
<P>
The show, now in its seventh month on the West End and due to bow on Broadway 
early next year, earned five nominations, including best musical, best actor in 
a musical and best director of a musical. Andrew Lloyd Webber's "Aspects of 
Love," expected to be its principal rival, earned no nominations. The winners 
will be announced April 8. BETH KLEID 
