</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The NHL Board of Governors, meeting in Rosemont, Ill., did not reach a decision 
on the proposed move of the Minnesota North Stars to the San Francisco Bay 
Area, but passed an amendment to the league's bylaws that could make it easier 
for any team to change cities. 
</P>
<P>
Previously, NHL rules stipulated that a unanimous vote of the board of 
governors was needed to relocate a franchise. The change would allow a team to 
move with simple majority approval under certain circumstances. 
</P>
