<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: CAPITALS GET GOALIE LIUT FROM WHALERS IN TRADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Washington Capitals, seeking goaltending help for their playoff drive, 
acquired Mike Liut from the Hartford Whalers in exchange for journeyman left 
wing Yvon Corriveau on Monday, one day before the NHL trading deadline. 
</P>
<P>
Liut, 34, has a 2.64 goals-against average, second in the NHL to Montreal's 
Patrick Roy. Corriveau, 23, has nine goals and six assists through 50 games 
this season. 
</P>
<P>
In other trades, the Buffalo Sabres sent winger Kevin Maguire to Philadelphia 
for former King defenseman Jay Wells; and the Quebec Nordiques, already 
eliminated from the playoffs, traded veteran left wing Michel Goulet and 
goaltender Greg Millen to the Blackhawks for forwards Everett Sanipass and 
Daniel Vincelette and prospect Mario Doyon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
