<LENGTH>
<P>
95 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE DEATH OF HANK GATHERS; 
</P>
<P>
CBS DECIDES TO POSTPONE TELECAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CBS said Monday it postponed a show in which a basketball star collapses during 
a game to spare the feelings of friends and family of Hank Gathers. 
</P>
<P>
"Malcolm Takes a Shot," in which Kareem Abdul-Jabbar makes a cameo appearance, 
was scheduled for showing today. In it Jon Clair plays Malcolm Jones, a high 
school athlete who is stricken with an epileptic seizure during the final 
seconds of a game. 
</P>
<P>
"Out of concern for the family and friends of Hank Gathers we have decided to 
postpone tomorrow's broadcast . . . because of the nature of the story," CBS 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
