<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOP 20 DEFENSE CONTRACTORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
McDonnell Douglas Corp. is still the nation's biggest defense contractor, but 
Tenneco Inc. has plummeted from fourth to 21st on the Defense Department's list 
of arms makers, the Pentagon said. The department released its 1989 totals of 
prime contract awards to companies, showing St. Louis-based McDonnell Douglas 
with $8.6 billion of work last year led the list. 
</P>
