<TEXT>
<P>
ART &amp; COMMERCE: South Coast Repertory Theatre's 10 L.A. Drama Critics 
Awards (F1) are not the only distinctions for local dramatists. . . . Doug 
Rowe, artistic director of the Laguna Playhouse, appeared opposite Walter 
Matthau in Sunday's CBS movie "The Incident." . . . Did it mean big bucks? Not 
exactly. When the film's Australian production company, Qintex, filed for 
bankruptcy, "I got stuck for a rubber check of $1,500," the last installment of 
his $8,000 fee. . . . Also on the tube: Laguna Playhouse discovery Lisa Picotte 
of Buena Park, starring in last night's "His and Hers" sitcom on CBS. Kristina 
Lindgren and Mark I. Pinksy 
</P>
