<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kristina Lindgren and Mark I. Pinksy 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEED TO KNOW: Orange County is at the forefront of efforts to combat AIDS in 
the Latino community (E1), with good cause. . . . As of Jan. 31, 12.2% of the 
county's AIDS cases were Latinos, and of 807 AIDS deaths, 94 were Latino. . . . 
"I think we have an excellent outreach program," said county AIDS coordinator 
Penny Weismuller, adding that a photographic comic book about AIDS in Spanish 
that was produced in the county is now used statewide. Kristina Lindgren and 
Mark I. Pinksy 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
