<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
TASK FORCE TO STUDY SROS FOR HOMELESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA MASCARO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city has appointed three officials to serve on a countywide task force that 
will research the feasibility of building single room occupancy housing for the 
homeless. 
</P>
<P>
Joining the task force will be Councilman William D. Ehrle and Eric Nicoll and 
Bertha Chavoya of the city's Community Development Department. 
</P>
<P>
To date, representatives of 17 Orange County cities and county government have 
joined the task force, which has held informal meetings and is in the early 
stages of research. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana Mayor Daniel H. Young has set a goal of building one housing project 
of at least 200 units in each Orange County city.LISA MASCARO 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
