<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA HABRA; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCIL PAY RAISE WILL BE DISCUSSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID F. BURKE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Members of the City Council will consider voting themselves a pay raise at 
tonight's meeting. 
</P>
<P>
Councilman James Flora asked that a resolution be drafted that would increase 
the monthly stipend from $300 to $400. At the urging of other members, however, 
Mayor Beth Graham ordered that the amount be left blank. 
</P>
<P>
City Council salaries among 29 Orange County cities range from no pay at all, 
as in the cases of Seal Beach and Villa Park, to $690 monthly in Costa Mesa and 
Orange, said La Habra City Manager Lee Risner. 
</P>
<P>
La Habra's $300 monthly salary has been unchanged since 1982, Risner 
added.DAVID F. BURKE 
</P>
</TEXT>
