<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASEBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SANTA ANA VALLEY'S CROSBY SHUTS DOWN CORONA DEL MAR, 9-1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Scott Crosby didn't allow a hit for four innings as Santa Ana Valley High 
School defeated Corona del Mar, 9-1, in the first round of the Newport Elks' 
baseball tournament Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Crosby (1-0) struck out three and did not walk a batter. He was relieved in the 
fifth by Jose Arroyo, who gave up a run. Santa Ana Valley coaches pulled 
Crosby, who was six pitches shy of his early-season limit of 50. 
</P>
<P>
Crosby had two hits and a run batted in for Santa Ana Valley (1-0). Mike 
Murtaugh had two hits and two RBIs and Juan Sanchez had a hit and two RBIs for 
the Falcons. 
</P>
<P>
In other Newport tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
Foothill 11, Capistrano Valley 6 -- Kent Donnelly had a grand slam and pitched 
five innings, getting five strikeouts for host Foothill (1-0). 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 12, Mater Dei JV 5 -- Victor Franco hit a two-run home run and John 
Morales and Santiago Lopez each had three hits and scored three runs for host 
Santa Ana (1-0). 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 10, Orange 7 -- Tommy Smith had a two-run single and a sacrifice fly 
and Ralph Cedillo had two hits and two RBIs for Saddleback (3-0). Ruben 
Hernandez hit a three-run homer for Orange (0-3). 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo 2, Estancia 1 -- Greg Brannis of Estancia pitched a one-hitter 
with 11 strikeouts, but Mission Viejo scored two unearned runs. Steve Evans 
(1-0) allowed three hits for visiting Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo's only hit was a two-out double in the fifth by Mark Newman. 
Pinch-runner Alex Diaz scored on a throwing error. 
</P>
<P>
In the championship bracket of the Loara tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Fountain Valley 11, Diamond Bar 6 -- Derek Brown had two hits, including a 
three-run homer, and four RBIs for host Fountain Valley (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
El Dorado 4, Riverside North 1 -- Pitcher Andy Brazeel allowed three hits and 
struck out six for host El Dorado (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
Lakewood 5, Laguna Hills 0 -- Laguna Hills' Kevin Lovengier had a two-out 
single in the seventh inning to break up a no-hitter by Lakewood's Dave Reeser. 
</P>
<P>
Ocean View 13, Kennedy 1 -- Dan Hernandez had three hits and scored four runs, 
and sophomore Micah Edwardson had an RBI triple and three-run home run for host 
Ocean View (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
Sunny Hills 14, Los Alamitos 6 -- Brian Veronda had three hits, scored two runs 
and had two RBIs for host Sunny Hills (2-2). 
</P>
<P>
Katella 11, Magnolia 4 -- Eric Boyd had three hits and three RBIs and Dennis 
Briggs hit a solo home run for Katella (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
Savanna 6, University 3 -- Doug Sutton's two RBI keyed a four-run fifth inning 
for Savanna (2-0). University dropped to 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
In the consolation bracket: 
</P>
<P>
Pacifica 7, Western 6 -- Chris Castellano doubled in two runs to give Pacifica 
the lead in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
Newbury Park 6, El Toro 3 -- Dave Owens had two hits and two RBIs for El Toro 
(0-2). 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta 8, Irvine 7 -- Anthony Beltran had a bases-loaded single in the 
seventh to drive in Matt Logan with the game-winning run. Logan had started the 
inning with a double. Mike Seal had three hits with two RBIs for Irvine (0-2). 
</P>
<P>
Villa Park 3, Los Amigos 2 -- Danny Strapp walked, stole second, went to third 
on a throwing error and scored on sacrifice fly by James Hong in the seventh 
for host Villa Park (1-1). 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 4, Loara 0 -- Kenny Mays pitched six-plus innings, allowing 
six hits and striking out six for the victory at Boysen Park in Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
San Clemente 7, Downey 2 -- Doug DeLaGarza hit a two-run home run, and had an 
RBI double to lead host San Clemente (1-1). He also threw a three-hitter with 
five strikeouts. Ken Dolan hit a solo home run for San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 4, Marina 2 -- Catcher David Dzurilla threw out three runners trying to 
steal, had three hits, including two doubles, and two RBIs for Cypress (1-1). 
Marina is 0-2. 
</P>
<P>
Santiago 5, Anaheim 3 -- Kip Cruz had a triple and two RBIs to lead Santiago 
(3-1) in the consolation round. 
</P>
