<TEXT>
<P>
Members of the Writers Guild of America overwhelmingly approved an agreement 
with CBS for a new three-year contract that provides wage increases and other 
benefits, it was announced today. 
</P>
<P>
Mona Mangan, executive director of the Writers Guild, East, said the approval, 
which came in voting in Los Angeles and New York on Monday, was "most 
gratifying." 
</P>
<P>
She said the vote was 87.2% in favor of a contract covering 325 CBS television 
and radio employees on both coasts that is retroactive to last Friday. The 
agreement provides for an immediate wage increase of 5% and another for the 
same amount Sept. 1, 1991. 
