AOKI/WESTIN TO BUY SWISSOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ZURICH, Switzerland 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Swissair, the national airline of Switzerland, today announced the sale of its 
worldwide Swissotel hotel operations to the giant Aoki/Westin group of Japan. 
</P>
<P>
The price was not disclosed pending final agreement. 
</P>
<P>
Swissotel fully owns or has a major stake in 12 luxury hotels including four in 
the United States -- the Drake in New York, the Lafayette in Boston, the Swiss 
Grand in Chicago and the Swiss Grand in Atlanta. 
</P>
<P>
Swissotel, which has a total of 3,130 employees, also manages five other 
leading hotels. 
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Swissair said the sale will become final as soon as smaller 
shareholders in some of the hotels approve the transaction. 
</P>
<P>
"It was decided to seek a buyer because Swissotel failed to reach the total of 
30 or so hotels which were seen necessary to make operations profitable," the 
spokesman said. "Aoki/Westin was chosen because it will give Swissair access to 
nearly 100 top hotels around the world." 
</P>
