<HEADLINE>
<P>
HURRICANES MAY GO TO ALL-SPORTS LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MORGANTOWN, W.Va. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Miami Hurricanes are considering a move from independent status to the 
Atlantic 10 Conference in basketball when Penn State joins the Big 10, an 
athletic official said. 
</P>
<P>
"We have had some discussions with the Atlantic 10," Miami Associate Athletic 
Director Larry Wall told the Dominion Post of Morgantown in today's editions. 
"That's about where it is right now: discussions. 
</P>
<P>
"We're looking at anything that makes sense, whether it be an all-sports 
conference or whether it be to remain independent in football." 
</P>
<P>
In recent months, Eastern football independents have talked about forming an 
all-sports conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
