<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
PEREZ MAY MISS SOCCER FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
U.S. midfield soccer star Hugo Perez said today he may miss this summer's World 
Cup finals in Italy after breaking a leg in a match on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Perez, who plays for French second division side Red Star of Paris, broke a 
fibula after coming on as a second-half substitute in the 2-1 victory at 
Gueugnon. 
</P>
<P>
The El Salvador-born player, a naturalized U.S. citizen, said he would be in 
plaster for three to six weeks but still has hopes of being fit in time for the 
finals. 
</P>
<P>
Perez, who missed most of the qualifying games because of a groin injury, said 
it would be up to the U.S. federation to decide whether he should go to Italy. 
</P>
<P>
The United States has qualified for the World Cup finals for the first time in 
40 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
