<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAND DEVIL WINS AT AQUEDUCT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sand Devil led all the way and breezed to a six-length victory in the $34,000 
Make Amends purse at Aqueduct on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The winner, coupled in the wagering with Indian Navy, was ridden by James Bruin 
and carried 117 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
Slick Jack, 117, took second place in the seven-horse field under Angel Cordero 
Jr. 
</P>
<P>
The victory was the first in four starts for Sand Devil, which went 1 1/8 on 
the fast track in 1:51 2/5. 
</P>
<P>
The winning entry returned $5.80, $2.80 and $2.80. Slick Jack paid $2.60 and 
$2.60 and Adam's Blend was $3.60 to show. 
</P>
<P>
At Sportsman's Park in Chicago, Quintillion, ridden by Mark Guidry, charged 
from 20 lengths behind the leader with half a mile left in the $20,000 American 
Prince Purse to score a 2 1/4 lengths victory Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Dvoik finished second and Royal Bonus rallied for third in the one-mile 
attraction, which matched a field of seven 4-year-olds and up. The race was 
held over a fast track as heavy snow fell. 
</P>
<P>
Quintillion, the 9-5 favorite, was timed in 1:41 2/5 and paid $5.60, $2.80 and 
$2.40. Dvoik, a 4-1 shot, paid $4.20 and $2.60. Royal Bonus, the 2-1 second 
choice, paid $2.20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
