Photo, A Perm for a Pachyderm Burnett Park keepers in Syracuse, N.Y., give 
Asian elephant Babe her morning scrub today. The 7,400-pound elephant is one of 
two expectant mothers in the zoo's herd. At 36, Babe will be the oldest 
elephant in the nation to give birth later this month or in early April, 
officials say. Only one or two elephants are born annually in North America. 
